## Detailed Flow

### 5.1 Determine Signing Order
```javascript
// Sort by announcement arrival time (first to confirm signs first)
signing_order = majority_nodes.sort((a, b) => {
  ann_a = announcements.find(a => a.node_id === ann.node_id);
  ann_b = announcements.find(b => b.node_id === ann.node_id);
  return ann_a.timestamp - ann_b.timestamp;
});

// Ties broken by node_id ULID
// Example: ["A", "B"] (A arrived first)
```

### 5.2 First Signer (A)
```javascript
checkpoint_data = {
  round: round_number,
  state_hash: majority_hash,
  timestamp: Date.now(),
  signatures: []  // Empty for first signer
};

sig_A3 = sign(A_private_key, checkpoint_data);

checkpoint_data.signatures.push({
  node_id: "A",
  signature: sig_A3
});

// Pass to next signer (B)
POST https://B.endpoint/sync/seal
{ checkpoint_data }
```

### 5.3 Second Signer (B)
```javascript
// Receive from A
checkpoint_data = req.body;

// Verify A's signature
if (!verifySignature(checkpoint_data, sig_A3, A_pubkey)) {
  throw new Error("Invalid signature from A");
}

// Add my signature
sig_B3 = sign(B_private_key, checkpoint_data);

checkpoint_data.signatures.push({
  node_id: "B",
  signature: sig_B3
});

// Check if we have enough signatures
if (checkpoint_data.signatures.length >= quorum_size) {
  // Checkpoint complete!
  checkpoint_complete = true;

  // Notify all signers
  for (signer of signing_order) {
    POST https://{signer.endpoint}/sync/complete
    { checkpoint_data }
  }
}
```

### 5.4 Timeout Handling
```javascript
